data.enText: maneuver

data.chText: 细致巧妙的移动；机动动作
data.enText: a movement performed with care and skill

data.chText: 复杂的 / 熟练的移动
data.enText: a complicated/skilful manoeuvre

data.chText: 驾驶测试中会要求你做几个标准的机动动作。
data.enText: You will be asked to perform some standard manoeuvres during your driving test.
a clever plan, action or movement that is used to give sb an advantage
diplomatic manoeuvres

data.chText: 国际象棋中复杂的应对手段
data.enText: a complex manoeuvre in a game of chess
military exercises involving a large number of soldiers, ships, etc.

data.chText: 军队在沙漠中进行军事演习。
data.enText: The army is on manoeuvres in the desert.
freedom of/room for manoeuvre

data.chText: 改变事态的机会；回旋余地
data.enText: the chance to change the way that sth happens and influence decisions that are made

data.chText: （使谨慎或熟练地）移动，运动；转动
data.enText: to move or turn skilfully or carefully; to move or turn sth skilfully or carefully

data.chText: 那些游艇灵活地寻找位置。
data.enText: The yachts manoeuvred for position.

data.chText: 几乎没有什么活动空间。
data.enText: There was very little room to manoeuvre.

data.chText: 她小心翼翼地将车开进了车库。
data.enText: She manoeuvred the car carefully into the garage.
to control or influence a situation in a skilful but sometimes dishonest way

data.chText: 新法律没给我们留下多少回旋的余地。
data.enText: The new laws have left us little room to manoeuvre (= not much opportunity to change or influence a situation) .

data.chText: 她施展手腕使自己进入了公司最高领导层。
data.enText: She manoeuvred her way to the top of the company.
freedom of/room for manoeuvre

data.chText: 改变事态的机会；回旋余地
data.enText: the chance to change the way that sth happens and influence decisions that are made

tr: an action aimed at evading an opponent
a move made to gain a tactical end
a deliberate coordinated movement requiring dexterity and skill
example: the runner was out on a play by the shortstop

tr: a plan for attaining a particular goal
perform a movement in military or naval tactics in order to secure an advantage in attack or defense
act in order to achieve a certain goal
example: He maneuvered to get the chairmanship
She maneuvered herself into the directorship

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 maneuver

value.def: If you manoeuvre something into or out of an awkward position, you skilfully move it there.

example.ex: We attempted to manoeuvre the canoe closer to him...
example.tran: 我们试图让独木舟靠他更近一些。

example.ex: I manoeuvred my way among the tables to the back corner of the place...
example.tran: 我在桌子中间穿行，来到后面的角落里。

example.ex: The pilot instinctively maneuvered to avoid them.
example.tran: 飞行员本能地驾机避开他们。

example.ex: ...a ship capable of high speed and rapid manoeuvre.
example.tran: 速度快、机动性强的轮船

value.def: If you manoeuvre a situation, you change it in a clever and skilful way so that you can benefit from it.

example.ex: The authorities have to manoeuvre the markets into demanding a cut in interest rates...
example.tran: 当局不得不干预市场，迫其提出削减利率的要求。

example.ex: He brilliantly manoeuvred himself back to power...
example.tran: 他依靠手腕巧妙地重掌权力。
他那无人能及的运筹帷幄的政治手段

example.ex: ...his manoeuvrings on the matter of free trade.
example.tran: 他在自由贸易问题上耍的花招

value.def: Military manoeuvres are training exercises which involve the movement of soldiers and equipment over a large area.

example.ex: Allied troops begin maneuvers tomorrow to show how quickly forces could be mobilized in case of a new invasion...
example.tran: 盟军明日演习，来展示一旦发生新的入侵，其集结速度之快。

example.ex: The camp was used for military manoeuvres.
example.tran: 这个营地被用于军事演习。

trans: 作出改变的机会;回旋的余地
